<div id="js-estimate">
  <p>
    Based on what you’ve told us, if you use your <%= number_to_currency(pot) %> pension pot to take an adjustable income, you could get:

    <strong class="calculator__estimate__number t-calculator-tax-free-lump-sum">
      <%= number_to_currency(estimate[:tax_free_lump_sum]) %> tax free
    </strong>

    and from the <span class="t-calculator-taxable-portion"><%= number_to_currency(estimate[:taxable_portion]) %></span> left over:

    <strong class="calculator__estimate__number">
      your monthly income of <%= number_to_currency(desired_monthly_income) %>
      would last until you're <span class="t-calculator-age-for-desired-income"><%= estimate[:desired_income_with_pot_growth_lasts_until] %></span>
    </strong>
  </p>
</div>

<p>
  <label for="slider">Try with another income</label>
  <%= render 'components/slider', {
      id: 'slider',
      target: '#desired_monthly_income',
      option: 'adjustable-income',
      text_before: '£',
      initial_value: desired_monthly_income,
      min: 50,
      max: desired_monthly_income.to_f * 5,
      step: 50
  } %>
</p>

<ul class="t-calculator-notes">
  <li class="t-calculator-life-expectancy-income">
    An average life expectancy for someone born in the same year as you is <%= estimate[:life_expectancy] %> years. You could take a monthly income of <%= number_to_currency(estimate[:monthly_income_until_life_expectancy]) %> which would last until then.
  </li>
  <li>Your monthly income is subject to income tax.</li>
  <li>This is an estimate based the amount in your pot growing at a rate of about <%= estimate[:growth_interest_rate].to_i %>% per year — this may vary.</li>
</ul>
